## 🟢 Stage 1 — Foundations

### What is a Database?
- [✅] Understand: database vs DBMS vs SQL
- [✅] Understand: relational vs non-relational
- [✅] Install MySQL + MySQL Workbench
- [✅] Run: SHOW DATABASES, CREATE DATABASE, USE

### Tables & Data Types
- [✅] Learn core types: INT, VARCHAR, TEXT, DATE, BOOLEAN, DECIMAL
- [ ] Understand NULL vs empty string
- [ ] Practice: CREATE TABLE students

### INSERT & SELECT
- [ ] Practice: INSERT INTO ... VALUES
- [ ] Practice: SELECT * and SELECT specific columns

### UPDATE & DELETE
- [ ] Practice: UPDATE ... SET ... WHERE
- [ ] Practice: DELETE FROM ... WHERE
- [ ] Understand danger of missing WHERE clause

### Filtering with WHERE
- [ ] Practice: =, >, <, !=
- [ ] Practice: BETWEEN, LIKE, IN

### Sorting & Limiting
- [ ] Practice: ORDER BY ASC/DESC
- [ ] Practice: LIMIT

### Aggregate Functions
- [ ] Practice: COUNT(), AVG(), MAX(), MIN(), SUM()

### GROUP BY & HAVING
- [ ] Practice: GROUP BY
- [ ] Practice: HAVING (filter after grouping)
- [ ] Understand difference: WHERE vs HAVING

### Stage 1 Project: Library Book Tracker
- [ ] Create table: books (id, title, author, genre, year_published, available)
- [ ] Insert 10 books
- [ ] Query: all available books
- [ ] Query: books by genre
- [ ] Query: newest 5 books
- [ ] Push: stage-1-basics/library-tracker.sql
- [ ] Write stage-1-basics/README.md and push

