## 🔵 Stage 2 — Intermediate Queries

### Primary Keys & Foreign Keys
- [ ] Understand PRIMARY KEY and AUTO_INCREMENT
- [ ] Understand FOREIGN KEY and relationships
- [ ] Practice creating two related tables

### INNER JOIN
- [ ] Understand what a JOIN does
- [ ] Practice: INNER JOIN ... ON

### LEFT JOIN & RIGHT JOIN
- [ ] Practice: LEFT JOIN (keep all left rows)
- [ ] Practice: RIGHT JOIN
- [ ] Understand NULL rows in results

### Multiple JOINs
- [ ] Practice joining 3 tables
- [ ] Use table aliases (s, c, g)

### Subqueries
- [ ] Practice subquery in WHERE clause
- [ ] Practice subquery with IN

### String Functions
- [ ] Practice: UPPER(), LOWER(), CONCAT()
- [ ] Practice: LENGTH(), SUBSTRING()

### Date & Time Functions
- [ ] Practice: NOW(), CURDATE(), YEAR(), MONTH()
- [ ] Practice: DATEDIFF()

### CASE Statements
- [ ] Practice: CASE WHEN ... THEN ... ELSE ... END
- [ ] Build an age group classifier

### DISTINCT & NULL Handling
- [ ] Practice: SELECT DISTINCT
- [ ] Practice: IS NULL, IS NOT NULL
- [ ] Practice: COALESCE()

### Views
- [ ] Understand what a view is
- [ ] Practice: CREATE VIEW ... AS SELECT ...
- [ ] Query a view like a table

### Stage 2 Project: Student Enrollment System
- [ ] Create tables: students, courses, enrollments, grades
- [ ] Query: top 5 students by GPA
- [ ] Query: courses with most enrollments
- [ ] Query: students with no grades yet
- [ ] Create 2 views
- [ ] Push project + write stage-2-queries/README.md

