## 🟡 Stage 3 — Database Design

### Normalization: 1NF
- [ ] Understand atomic values
- [ ] Identify and fix a bad table design

### Normalization: 2NF & 3NF
- [ ] Understand partial dependencies (2NF)
- [ ] Understand transitive dependencies (3NF)
- [ ] Refactor a table to 3NF

### Entity Relationship Diagrams (ERDs)
- [ ] Learn: entities, attributes, relationships
- [ ] Learn: One-to-One, One-to-Many, Many-to-Many
- [ ] Draw ERD for Library Tracker
- [ ] Draw ERD for Enrollment System

### Indexes
- [ ] Understand why indexes speed up queries
- [ ] Practice: CREATE INDEX, SHOW INDEXES, DROP INDEX
- [ ] Run EXPLAIN before and after adding index

### Constraints
- [ ] Practice: NOT NULL, UNIQUE, CHECK, DEFAULT
- [ ] Build a products table using all constraints

### Transactions
- [ ] Understand what a transaction is
- [ ] Practice: START TRANSACTION, COMMIT, ROLLBACK
- [ ] Build a bank transfer example

### ACID Properties
- [ ] Learn: Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability
- [ ] Map each property to a real-world scenario

### Stored Procedures
- [ ] Understand what a stored procedure is
- [ ] Practice: CREATE PROCEDURE ... BEGIN ... END
- [ ] Call a procedure with CALL

### Stage 3 Project: E-commerce Database
- [ ] Draw ERD first (before writing SQL)
- [ ] Create tables: users, products, orders, order_items, categories
- [ ] Apply 1NF, 2NF, 3NF
- [ ] Add indexes on frequently queried columns
- [ ] Use transaction for order placement
- [ ] Push project + write stage-3-design/README.md

