## 🟠 Stage 4 — Advanced MySQL

### EXPLAIN & Query Optimization
- [ ] Run EXPLAIN on a slow-looking query
- [ ] Identify type=ALL (full scan) as a red flag
- [ ] Add an index to improve it

### Triggers
- [ ] Understand BEFORE vs AFTER triggers
- [ ] Create an audit log table
- [ ] Build a trigger that logs every DELETE

### User Management & Security
- [ ] Practice: CREATE USER, GRANT, REVOKE
- [ ] Create a read-only user and a read-write user
- [ ] Understand SQL injection concept

### Backup & Restore
- [ ] Backup a database with mysqldump
- [ ] Restore it into a new database

### Window Functions
- [ ] Understand: RANK(), ROW_NUMBER(), DENSE_RANK()
- [ ] Practice: OVER (PARTITION BY ... ORDER BY ...)

### CTEs (Common Table Expressions)
- [ ] Understand WITH ... AS (...)
- [ ] Rewrite a subquery as a CTE

### JSON in MySQL
- [ ] Create a table with a JSON column
- [ ] Insert and query JSON data
- [ ] Use ->>'$.key' syntax

### Stage 4 Project: Hospital Management System
- [ ] Create tables: patients, doctors, appointments, prescriptions, billing
- [ ] Add triggers for audit logging
- [ ] Build stored procedures for common operations
- [ ] Use window functions for doctor performance report
- [ ] Create restricted users (doctor role vs admin role)
- [ ] Push project + write stage-4-advanced/README.md

